{
  "stanzas": [
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "number": 1,
          "text": "When in our music God is glorified,"
        },
        {
          "number": 2,
          "text": "And adoration leaves no room for pride,"
        },
        {
          "number": 3,
          "text": "It is as though the whole creation cried:"
        },
        {
          "number": 4,
          "text": "Alleluia!"
        }
      ],
      "number": 1
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "number": 1,
          "text": "How oft, in making music, we have found"
        },
        {
          "number": 2,
          "text": "A new dimension in the world of sound,"
        },
        {
          "number": 3,
          "text": "As worship moved us to a more profound"
        },
        {
          "number": 4,
          "text": "Alleluia!"
        }
      ],
      "number": 2
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "number": 1,
          "text": "And did not Jesus sing a psalm that night"
        },
        {
          "number": 2,
          "text": "When utmost evil strove against the light?"
        },
        {
          "number": 3,
          "text": "Then let us sing for whom He won the fight:"
        },
        {
          "number": 4,
          "text": "Alleluia!"
        }
      ],
      "number": 3
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "number": 1,
          "text": "Let every instrument be used for praise;"
        },
        {
          "number": 2,
          "text": "Let all rejoice who have a voice to raise;"
        },
        {
          "number": 3,
          "text": "And may God give us faith to sing always:"
        },
        {
          "number": 4,
          "text": "Alleluia!"
        }
      ],
      "number": 4
    }
  ],
  "title": "When in Our Music God is Glorified"
}
